 needs met in advance at while room negotiations occured.
 They cannot anticipate the iterative nature of interdepartmental planning
 and the chain reaction which can be caused by plan changes within one particula
r departement.
 This is not a problem solong as the chain of rection to scheduling changes
 can be dealt with within the assigned resources and their availability.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This brings us to real weakness in the current modeling and workflow the
 visibility and availability in Untis of resources used by multiple departments.
 Aside from the issue of the freshness and visibility of resource usage
 across departments addressed in concurrency 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand vpageref
reference "Concurrency"

